\cb3 Summary of the paper (Summarize the main claims/contributions of the paper.):\cb1 \
\cb3 The authors present semi-implicit variational inference (SIVI), a form of variational inference in which the variational distribution q(z) is defined as the marginal of q(z, \uc0\u968 ) = q(z | \u968 ) q(\u968 ), where the mixing distribution q(\u968 ) can be an implicit, which is to say that we cannot evaluate the density. The authors define lower and upper bounds on the marginal likelihood that can be made tighter by increasing a number of samples K. The evaluate their approach on a negative binomial model, a model in which the variational distribution is not reparameterizable, Bayesian logistic regression and a semi-implicit variant of variational autoencoders.\cb1 \
