\cb3 This work introduces Semi-implicit variational inference (SIVI), which aims at constructing a flexible variational distribution by mixing an implicit distribution (e.g., based on a neural network transformation) with an explicit one, while maintaining a tractable optimization problem via an asymptotically exact surrogate ELBO. \cb1 \
\
\cb3 This work provides an alternative to works that make use of implicit models to make the variational distribution more flexible but then rely on density ratio estimation to evaluate and optimize the ELBO. \cb1 \
